  45def fuzz_general_enum_type(
  46    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None,
  47    valid_values: Optional[str] = None,
  48    enum_list: Optional[list] = None,
  49) -> Union[str, int, float]:
  50    """Fuzz enum type
  51
  52    Enum type is xs:string, so valid value is string.
  53    Fuzzer should test values out of enum values.
  54
  55    Relevant modes: random, string, special-string,
  56        int, negative-int, float, negative-float
  57    """
  58    if enum_list is None or len(enum_list) == 0:
  59        raise ValueError("enum_list is None or empty list")
  60    enum_name = enum_list[0].__class__.__name__
  61
  62    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, enum_name)
  63
  64    match mode:
  65        case ParamFuzzMode.VALID:
  66            if valid_values is None:
  67                logger.warning(
  68                    "No valid value specified for type %s, "
  69                    "using default valid value randomly chosen from "
  70                    "%s enum.",
  71                    enum_name,
  72                    enum_name,
  73                )
  74                return random.choice(enum_list).value
  75            return valid_values
  76        case ParamFuzzMode.STRING:
  77            return gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 100))
  78        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_STRING:
  79            if valid_values is None:
  80                logger.warning(
  81                    "No valid value specified for ResponseCode, "
  82                    "using default valid value randomly chosen from "
  83                    "responseCodeType enum."
  84                )
  85                valid_values = random.choice(enum_list).value
  86            return gen_malicous_string(valid_string=valid_values)
  87        case ParamFuzzMode.INT:
  88            return gen_num()
  89        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_INT:
  90            return gen_num(negative_flag=True)
  91        case ParamFuzzMode.FLOAT:
  92            return gen_num(float_flag=True)
  93        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_FLOAT:
  94            return gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True)
  95        case _:
  96            if mode is not ParamFuzzMode.RANDOM:
  97                logger.warning(
  98                    "Invalid fuzzing mode for parameter with type "
  99                    "%s, using random mode.",
 100                    enum_name,
 101                )
 102            invalid_values = [
 103                gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 100)),
 104                gen_num(),
 105                gen_num(negative_flag=True),
 106                gen_num(float_flag=True),
 107                gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True),
 108            ]
 109            return random.choice(invalid_values)

 112def get_attr_conf_mode(
 113    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, attr_name: str = ""
 114) -> ParamFuzzMode:
 115    """Get fuzzing mode for attribute/field/parameter
 116    (these are used interchangeably)"""
 117
 118    attr_conf = check_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf)
 119    try:
 120        mode = ParamFuzzMode(attr_conf["Mode"])
 121    except ValueError:
 122        logger.warning(
 123            "Invalid fuzzing mode for %s, using random mode.", attr_name
 124        )
 125        mode = ParamFuzzMode.RANDOM
 126
 127    return mode

 130def general_datatype_fuzzing_method(
 131    required_fields: list,
 132    all_fields: list,
 133    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None,
 134    valid_values: Optional[dict] = None,
 135    pairs_name_method: Optional[dict] = None,
 136    method_name: str = "",
 137) -> dict:
 138    """General fuzz method for complex datatype"""
 139
 140    if attr_conf is None:
 141        attr_conf = {}
 142        for field in all_fields:
 143            attr_conf[field] = None
 144
 145    # attr_conf is dict => empty or not empty
 146    else:
 147        # attr_conf is empty => pass to all required fields {}
 148        # => fuzz with random mode for end parameter
 149        # {} means random mode for every required field/parameter
 150        if not attr_conf:
 151            for field in required_fields:
 152                attr_conf[field] = {}
 153        # attr_conf is not empty
 154        else:
 155            # RequiredParams are specified in config => override required_fields
 156            if "RequiredParams" in attr_conf:
 157                # Responsibility is up to user
 158                for field in attr_conf["RequiredParams"]:
 159                    if field not in attr_conf:
 160                        logger.warning(
 161                            "Required parameter %s is not specified in config for fuzzing method %s. ",
 162                            field,
 163                            method_name,
 164                        )
 165                        logger.warning("Fuzzing with random mode")
 166                required_fields = attr_conf["RequiredParams"]
 167                # Pop RequiredParams from attr_conf if present,
 168                # because for loop iterates through keys in attr_conf
 169                # which are Field/Parameter names
 170                attr_conf.pop("RequiredParams")
 171
 172            # Field is in required_fields
 173            # but user didn't specify mode => pass {} to each parameter
 174            # => fuzz with random mode for end parameter
 175            # So not specified parameter will be fuzzed with random mode
 176            for field in required_fields:
 177                if field not in attr_conf:
 178                    attr_conf[field] = {}
 179
 180    if valid_values is None:
 181        valid_values = {}
 182
 183    if isinstance(valid_values, list):
 184        valid_values = valid_values[0]
 185
 186    res_dict = {}
 187    # Here is because of keep consistency with other methods for complexTypes
 188    for name in attr_conf.keys():
 189        # Attribute is not specified in config dict => don't fuzz it
 190        # => valid mode
 191        if name not in valid_values:
 192            valid_values[name] = None
 193
 194        # Should never happen
 195        assert pairs_name_method is not None
 196        res_dict[name] = pairs_name_method[name](
 197            attr_conf=attr_conf[name], valid_values=valid_values[name]
 198        )
 199
 200    return res_dict
 201

 203def check_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None) -> dict:
 204    """This method checks if attr_conf is None or empty dict or dict without Mode key."""
 205    if attr_conf is None or len(attr_conf) == 0:
 206        attr_conf = {"Mode": "random"}
 207    elif "Mode" not in attr_conf:
 208        attr_conf["Mode"] = "random"
 209
 210    return attr_conf

 213def fuzz_schema_id(
 214    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[int] = None
 215) -> Union[str, int, float]:
 216    """Fuzz schema id
 217
 218    SchemaID is xs:unsignedByte, so valid value is in range 0-255.
 219    Fuzzer should test values out of range, for example -1, 256,
 220    or string instead of number.
 221
 222    Relevant modes: random, string, int, over-int,
 223        under-int, float, over-float, under-float
 224    """
 225
 226    # This is end parameter, so there is no passing None/{} to each sub parameter
 227    # => fuzz with random mode for end parameter
 228    # attr_conf == {}
 229
 230    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, "SchemaID")
 231
 232    return gen_invalid_unsigned_byte(mode=mode, valid_val=valid_values)

 255def fuzz_evse_id(
 256    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None
 257) -> Union[str, int, float]:
 258    """Fuzz evse id
 259
 260    Inconsistency in the standard. In some messages is EVSEID xs:string
 261    and in some messages is EVSEID xs:hexBinary.
 262
 263    EVSEID is type xs:string (in xml schema), (min length: 7, max length:37).
 264    If an SECC cannot provide such ID data,
 265    the value of the EVSEID is set to zero ("ZZ00000").
 266    The above definition is in SessionSetupRes, ChargingStatusRes.
 267
 268    EVSEID is type: xs:hexBinary, max length 32. (in CurrendDemandRes message).
 269    If an SECC cannot provide such ID data,
 270    the value of the EVSEID is set to zero (00hex).
 271
 272    Args:
 273        val_type (str): Type of EVSEID. Valid values: string, hexBinary.
 274            Differ between EVSEID type string and hexBinary based on message.
 275        mode: Fuzzing mode for EVSEID.
 276            Relevant modes: random, string, int, negative-int, float,
 277            negative-float, short-string, long-string, special-string,
 278            long-hex, special-hex.
 279            The modes with hex in name are only for EVSEID type hexBinary, but
 280            if user specify these modes for EVSEID type string, fuzzer will use
 281            them.
 282    """
 283    # This is end parameter, so there is no passing None/{} to each sub parameter
 284    # => fuzz with random mode for end parameter
 285    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, "EVSEID")
 286    # After this attr_conf is not None and contains Mode key
 287    if attr_conf is None:
 288        attr_conf = {"Mode": "random"}
 289
 290    assert attr_conf is not None
 291
 292    if "Type" not in attr_conf:
 293        attr_conf["Type"] = "string"
 294    val_type = attr_conf["Type"]
 295
 296    match mode:
 297        case ParamFuzzMode.VALID:
 298            if valid_values is None:
 299                # EVSEID type string
 300                if val_type == "string":
 301                    logger.warning(
 302                        "No valid value specified for EVSEID, "
 303                        "using default valid value from standard."
 304                    )
 305                    return "ZZ00000"
 306                # EVSEID type hexBinary
 307                logger.warning(
 308                    "No valid value specified for EVSEID, "
 309                    "using default valid value from standard."
 310                )
 311                return "00"
 312            return valid_values
 313        case ParamFuzzMode.STRING:
 314            # Length is valid for EVSEID type xs:string
 315            return gen_random_string(random.randint(7, 37))
 316        case ParamFuzzMode.SHORT_STRING:
 317            # Length is randomly chosen from 1-6 (min length is 7)
 318            return gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 6))
 319        case ParamFuzzMode.LONG_STRING:
 320            # Length is randomly chosen from 38-100 (max length is 37)
 321            return gen_random_string(random.randint(38, 100))
 322        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_STRING:
 323            return gen_malicous_string()
 324        case ParamFuzzMode.HEX:
 325            # Length is valid for EVSEID type xs:hexBinary
 326            return gen_invalid_hex_binary(random.randint(1, 32))
 327        case ParamFuzzMode.LONG_HEX:
 328            # valid max length is 32, method will gen > 32 + 1
 329            return gen_invalid_hex_binary(max_length=32)
 330        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_HEX:
 331            return gen_malicous_hex()
 332        case ParamFuzzMode.INT:
 333            return gen_num()
 334        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_INT:
 335            return gen_num(negative_flag=True)
 336        case ParamFuzzMode.FLOAT:
 337            return gen_num(float_flag=True)
 338        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_FLOAT:
 339            return gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True)
 340        case _:
 341            if mode is not ParamFuzzMode.RANDOM:
 342                logger.warning(
 343                    "Invalid fuzzing mode for parameter EVSEID with type "
 344                    "xs:string or xs:hexBinary, using random mode."
 345                )
 346            invalid_values = []
 347            invalid_num = gen_num()
 348            invalid_neg_num = gen_num(negative_flag=True)
 349            invalid_float_num = gen_num(float_flag=True)
 350            invalid_neg_float_num = gen_num(
 351                float_flag=True, negative_flag=True
 352            )
 353            invalid_values.append(invalid_num)
 354            invalid_values.append(invalid_neg_num)
 355            invalid_values.append(invalid_float_num)
 356            invalid_values.append(invalid_neg_float_num)
 357
 358            if val_type == "string":
 359                invalid_string_shorter = gen_random_string(
 360                    random.randint(1, 6)
 361                )
 362                invalid_string_longer = gen_random_string(
 363                    random.randint(38, 100)
 364                )
 365                invalid_values.append(invalid_string_shorter)
 366                invalid_values.append(invalid_string_longer)
 367            else:
 368                # No restriction for min length for hexBinary only for max
 369                # Max length for hexBinary is 32
 370                invalid_hex_longer = gen_invalid_hex_binary(max_length=32)
 371                invalid_values.append(invalid_hex_longer)
 372
 373            special_string = gen_malicous_string()
 374            invalid_values.append(special_string)
 375            special_hex = gen_malicous_hex()
 376            invalid_values.append(special_hex)
 377
 378            return random.choice(invalid_values)
 379

 381def fuzz_evse_timestamp(
 382    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[int] = None
 383) -> Union[str, int, float]:
 384    """Fuzz evse timestamp
 385
 386    Valid value is Unix timestamp, xs:long.
 387    The value can be -9223372036854775808 to 9223372036854775807 for xs:long.
 388
 389    For Unix timestamp negative value makes no sense, so fuzzer should test it.
 390
 391    Args:
 392        mode: Fuzzing mode for EVSETimestamp.
 393            Relevant modes: random, float, under-float, over-float,
 394            under-int, over-int, string, special-string,
 395    """
 396
 397    # This is end parameter, so there is no passing None/{} to each sub parameter
 398    # => fuzz with random mode for end parameter
 399    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, "EVSETimeStamp")
 400
 401    return gen_invalid_long(mode=mode, valid_val=valid_values)

 548def fuzz_service_name(
 549    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None
 550) -> Union[str, int, float]:
 551    """Fuzz service name
 552
 553    ServiceName is type xs:string (in xml schema), (maxLength: 32).
 554    """
 555    # This is end parameter, so there is no passing None/{} to each sub parameter
 556    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, "ServiceName")
 557
 558    match mode:
 559        case ParamFuzzMode.VALID:
 560            if valid_values is None:
 561                logger.warning(
 562                    "No valid value specified for ServiceName, "
 563                    "using default valid value randomly generated."
 564                    "Disclaimer: Generated value - meets the conditions for "
 565                    "length and type but may not meet the valid "
 566                    "value for particular parameter."
 567                )
 568                return gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 32))
 569            return valid_values
 570
 571        case ParamFuzzMode.LONG_STRING:
 572            return gen_random_string(random.randint(33, 100))
 573        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_STRING:
 574            return gen_malicous_string()
 575        case ParamFuzzMode.INT:
 576            return gen_num()
 577        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_INT:
 578            return gen_num(negative_flag=True)
 579        case ParamFuzzMode.FLOAT:
 580            return gen_num(float_flag=True)
 581        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_FLOAT:
 582            return gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True)
 583        case _:
 584            if mode is not ParamFuzzMode.RANDOM:
 585                logger.warning(
 586                    "Invalid fuzzing mode for parameter with type "
 587                    "xs:string, using random mode."
 588                )
 589            invalid_string = gen_random_string(random.randint(33, 100))
 590            invalid_special_string = gen_malicous_string()
 591            invalid_num = gen_num()
 592            invalid_neg_num = gen_num(negative_flag=True)
 593            invalid_float_num = gen_num(float_flag=True)
 594            invalid_neg_float_num = gen_num(
 595                negative_flag=True, float_flag=True
 596            )
 597
 598            return random.choice(
 599                [
 600                    invalid_string,
 601                    invalid_special_string,
 602                    invalid_num,
 603                    invalid_neg_num,
 604                    invalid_float_num,
 605                    invalid_neg_float_num,
 606                ]

 772def fuzz_parameter_name(
 773    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None
 774) -> Union[str, int, float]:
 775    """Fuzz parameter name. In standard is defined as xs:string"""
 776    # This is end parameter, so there is no passing None/{} to each sub parameter
 777    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, "Parameter Name")
 778    if attr_conf is None or len(attr_conf) == 0:
 779        attr_conf = {"Mode": "random"}
 780    # After this attr_conf is not None and contains Mode key
 781    assert attr_conf is not None
 782
 783    if valid_values is None:
 784        if attr_conf["Mode"] == ParamFuzzMode.VALID:
 785            logger.warning(
 786                "No valid value specified for Parameter Name, "
 787                "using default valid value randomly chosen from "
 788                "parameter name examples from standard."
 789            )
 790        valid_values = random.choice(["Protocol", "Port"])
 791
 792    return gen_invalid_string(mode=mode, valid_val=valid_values)

 795def fuzz_parameter_type(
 796    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None
 797) -> str:
 798    """Fuzz parameter type, Mode can be valid or random."""
 799
 800    # Possible values for Parameter Type
 801    value_types = [
 802        "boolValue",
 803        "byteValue",
 804        "shortValue",
 805        "intValue",
 806        "physicalValue",
 807        "stringValue",
 808    ]
 809
 810    # This is end parameter, so there is no passing None/{} to each sub parameter
 811    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, "Parameter Type")
 812    # After this attr_conf is not None
 813
 814    if attr_conf is None or len(attr_conf) == 0:
 815        attr_conf = {"Mode": "random"}
 816    assert attr_conf is not None
 817
 818    if mode == ParamFuzzMode.VALID:
 819        if "value" not in attr_conf:
 820            logger.warning(
 821                "No valid value specified for Parameter Type, "
 822                "using default valid value randomly chosen from "
 823                "possible values for parameter type."
 824            )
 825            value_type = random.choice(value_types)
 826        value_type = attr_conf["value"]
 827    else:
 828        value_type = random.choice(value_types)
 829
 830    if value_type not in value_types:
 831        logger.warning("Invalid value type for Parameter, using random mode.")
 832        value_type = random.choice(value_types)  # => value_type is valid
 833
 834    return value_type

 887def fuzz_parameter(
 888    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[dict] = None
 889) -> dict:
 890    """Fuzz parameter
 891
 892    Parameter is complex type, so it has attributes and elements.
 893    In XSD defined as: parameterType.
 894    """
 895
 896    pairs_name_method = {
 897        "@Name": fuzz_parameter_name,
 898        "boolValue": fuzz_parameter_bool_value,
 899        "byteValue": fuzz_parameter_byte_value,
 900        "shortValue": fuzz_parameter_short_value,
 901        "intValue": fuzz_parameter_int_value,
 902        "physicalValue": fuzz_physical_value_type,
 903        "stringValue": fuzz_parameter_string_value,
 904    }
 905    required_fields = ["@Name"]
 906    all_fields = ["@Name"]
 907
 908    # Based on type add value_type to pairs_name_method
 909
 910    # Only in conf is "Name", but in XSD is attribute not element
 911    # therefor change it to @Name
 912    if attr_conf is None:
 913        attr_conf = {}
 914    if "Name" in attr_conf:
 915        attr_conf["@Name"] = attr_conf.pop("Name")
 916
 917    if "Type" not in attr_conf:
 918        attr_conf["Type"] = None
 919
 920    value_type = fuzz_parameter_type(attr_conf=attr_conf["Type"])
 921    required_fields.append(value_type)
 922    all_fields.append(value_type)
 923    attr_conf.pop("Type")
 924    if "Value" in attr_conf:
 925        attr_conf[value_type] = attr_conf.pop("Value")
 926    else:
 927        attr_conf[value_type] = None
 928    # After this in attr_conf is only @Name and value_type
 929    # value_type is one of the value_types => for ex.:
 930    # attr_conf {"@Name": "Port", "intValue": 12}
 931
 932    res_dict = {}
 933    # Call general method for fuzzing complexType
 934    res_dict = general_datatype_fuzzing_method(
 935        required_fields=required_fields,
 936        all_fields=all_fields,
 937        attr_conf=attr_conf,
 938        valid_values=valid_values,
 939        pairs_name_method=pairs_name_method,
 940    )
 941    return res_dict
 942

1008def fuzz_gen_challenge(
1009    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None
1010) -> Union[str, int, float]:
1011    """Fuzz gen challenge
1012
1013    GenChallenge is type base64Binary (in xml schema), (length 16).
1014    GenChallenge should be exactly 16 bytes long (128 bits).
1015
1016    From ISO15118-2 example on page 330, length is length of the data before
1017    base64 encoding. Use of UTF-8 encoding is required.
1018    Example: 'U29tZSBSYW5kb20gRGF0YQ==' => 'Some Random Data'
1019    """
1020    # This is end parameter, so there is no passing None/{} to each sub parameter
1021    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, "GenChallenge")
1022
1023    # str to base64 encoding => str to bytes => bytes to base64 encoding
1024    # base64.b64encode(str.encode('utf-8')) or base64.b64encode(bytes(str, 'utf-8'))
1025    # base64 to str => base64 to bytes => bytes to str
1026    # base64.b64decode(base64_encoded_str).decode('utf-8')
1027    # Convert mode to enum
1028
1029    match mode:
1030        case ParamFuzzMode.VALID:
1031            if valid_values is None:
1032                # Generate valid base64 binary, because the length is 16
1033                # => valid value is base64 encoded 16 bytes long binary
1034                return gen_invalid_base64_binary(length=16)
1035            return valid_values
1036        case ParamFuzzMode.LONG_BASE64:
1037            # Generate base64 binary with length > 16
1038            return gen_invalid_base64_binary(max_length=16)
1039        case ParamFuzzMode.SHORT_BASE64:
1040            # Generate base64 binary with length < 16
1041            return gen_invalid_base64_binary(min_length=16)
1042        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_BASE64:
1043            if valid_values is None:
1044                valid_values = gen_invalid_base64_binary(length=16)
1045            return gen_malicous_base64(valid_base64=valid_values)
1046        case ParamFuzzMode.INT:
1047            return gen_num()
1048        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_INT:
1049            return gen_num(negative_flag=True)
1050        case ParamFuzzMode.FLOAT:
1051            return gen_num(float_flag=True)
1052        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_FLOAT:
1053            return gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True)
1054        case ParamFuzzMode.STRING:
1055            return gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 100))
1056        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_STRING:
1057            return gen_malicous_string()
1058        case _:
1059            if mode is not ParamFuzzMode.RANDOM:
1060                logger.warning(
1061                    "Invalid fuzzing mode for parameter with type "
1062                    "base64Binary, using random mode."
1063                )
1064            invalid_values = [
1065                gen_invalid_base64_binary(length=16),
1066                gen_invalid_base64_binary(max_length=16),
1067                gen_invalid_base64_binary(min_length=16),
1068                gen_malicous_base64(),
1069                gen_num(),
1070                gen_num(negative_flag=True),
1071                gen_num(float_flag=True),
1072                gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True),
1073                gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 100)),
1074                gen_malicous_string(),
1075            ]
1076            return random.choice(invalid_values)
1077

1857def fuzz_retry_counter(mode: str = "valid") -> Union[str, int, float]:
1858    """Fuzz retry counter
1859
1860    If the ResponseCode was 'FAILED_NoCertificateAvailable' or 'FAILED_ContractCanceled',
1861    this field contains information, when the EVCC should try to get
1862    the new certificate again.
1863    Type is xs:short (in xml schema), so valid values: -32768 to 32767, but
1864    it has restriction.
1865
1866    The following entries are possible:
1867        x > 0: after x days
1868        0: immediately (at next charging)
1869        -1: never
1870
1871    Use this fuzz method only if ResponseCode is 'FAILED_NoCertificateAvailable'
1872    or 'FAILED_ContractCanceled'.
1873    """
1874
1875    # Convert mode to enum
1876    try:
1877        mode = ParamFuzzMode(mode)

 46def fuzz_general_enum_type(

 51    """Fuzz enum type

def general_datatype_fuzzing_method( required_fields: list, all_fields: list, attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[dict] = None, pairs_name_method: Optional[dict] = None, method_name: str = '') -> dict: 
131def general_datatype_fuzzing_method(
132    required_fields: list,
133    all_fields: list,
134    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None,
135    valid_values: Optional[dict] = None,
136    pairs_name_method: Optional[dict] = None,
137    method_name: str = "",
138) -> dict:
139    """General fuzz method for complex datatype"""
140
141    if attr_conf is None:
142        attr_conf = {}
143        for field in all_fields:
144            attr_conf[field] = None
145
146    # attr_conf is dict => empty or not empty
147    else:
148        # attr_conf is empty => pass to all required fields {}
149        # => fuzz with random mode for end parameter
150        # {} means random mode for every required field/parameter
151        if not attr_conf:
152            for field in required_fields:
153                attr_conf[field] = {}
154        # attr_conf is not empty
155        else:
156            # RequiredParams are specified in config => override required_fields
157            if "RequiredParams" in attr_conf:
158                # Responsibility is up to user
159                for field in attr_conf["RequiredParams"]:
160                    if field not in attr_conf:
161                        logger.warning(
162                            "Required parameter %s is not specified in config for fuzzing method %s. ",
163                            field,
164                            method_name,
165                        )
166                        logger.warning("Fuzzing with random mode")
167                required_fields = attr_conf["RequiredParams"]
168                # Pop RequiredParams from attr_conf if present,
169                # because for loop iterates through keys in attr_conf
170                # which are Field/Parameter names
171                attr_conf.pop("RequiredParams")
172
173            # Field is in required_fields
174            # but user didn't specify mode => pass {} to each parameter
175            # => fuzz with random mode for end parameter
176            # So not specified parameter will be fuzzed with random mode
177            for field in required_fields:
178                if field not in attr_conf:
179                    attr_conf[field] = {}
180
181    if valid_values is None:
182        valid_values = {}
183
184    if isinstance(valid_values, list):
185        valid_values = valid_values[0]
186
187    res_dict = {}
188    # Here is because of keep consistency with other methods for complexTypes
189    for name in attr_conf.keys():
190        # Attribute is not specified in config dict => don't fuzz it
191        # => valid mode
192        if name not in valid_values:
193            valid_values[name] = None
194
195        # Should never happen
196        assert pairs_name_method is not None
197        res_dict[name] = pairs_name_method[name](
198            attr_conf=attr_conf[name], valid_values=valid_values[name]
199        )
200
201    return res_dict

def fuzz_evse_id( attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None) -> Union[str, int, float]: 
256def fuzz_evse_id(
257    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None
258) -> Union[str, int, float]:
259    """Fuzz evse id
260
261    Inconsistency in the standard. In some messages is EVSEID xs:string
262    and in some messages is EVSEID xs:hexBinary.
263
264    EVSEID is type xs:string (in xml schema), (min length: 7, max length:37).
265    If an SECC cannot provide such ID data,
266    the value of the EVSEID is set to zero ("ZZ00000").
267    The above definition is in SessionSetupRes, ChargingStatusRes.
268
269    EVSEID is type: xs:hexBinary, max length 32. (in CurrendDemandRes message).
270    If an SECC cannot provide such ID data,
271    the value of the EVSEID is set to zero (00hex).
272
273    Args:
274        val_type (str): Type of EVSEID. Valid values: string, hexBinary.
275            Differ between EVSEID type string and hexBinary based on message.
276        mode: Fuzzing mode for EVSEID.
277            Relevant modes: random, string, int, negative-int, float,
278            negative-float, short-string, long-string, special-string,
279            long-hex, special-hex.
280            The modes with hex in name are only for EVSEID type hexBinary, but
281            if user specify these modes for EVSEID type string, fuzzer will use
282            them.
283    """
284    # This is end parameter, so there is no passing None/{} to each sub parameter
285    # => fuzz with random mode for end parameter
286    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, "EVSEID")
287    # After this attr_conf is not None and contains Mode key
288    if attr_conf is None:
289        attr_conf = {"Mode": "random"}
290
291    assert attr_conf is not None
292
293    if "Type" not in attr_conf:
294        attr_conf["Type"] = "string"
295    val_type = attr_conf["Type"]
296
297    match mode:
298        case ParamFuzzMode.VALID:
299            if valid_values is None:
300                # EVSEID type string
301                if val_type == "string":
302                    logger.warning(
303                        "No valid value specified for EVSEID, "
304                        "using default valid value from standard."
305                    )
306                    return "ZZ00000"
307                # EVSEID type hexBinary
308                logger.warning(
309                    "No valid value specified for EVSEID, "
310                    "using default valid value from standard."
311                )
312                return "00"
313            return valid_values
314        case ParamFuzzMode.STRING:
315            # Length is valid for EVSEID type xs:string
316            return gen_random_string(random.randint(7, 37))
317        case ParamFuzzMode.SHORT_STRING:
318            # Length is randomly chosen from 1-6 (min length is 7)
319            return gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 6))
320        case ParamFuzzMode.LONG_STRING:
321            # Length is randomly chosen from 38-100 (max length is 37)
322            return gen_random_string(random.randint(38, 100))
323        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_STRING:
324            return gen_malicous_string()
325        case ParamFuzzMode.HEX:
326            # Length is valid for EVSEID type xs:hexBinary
327            return gen_invalid_hex_binary(random.randint(1, 32))
328        case ParamFuzzMode.LONG_HEX:
329            # valid max length is 32, method will gen > 32 + 1
330            return gen_invalid_hex_binary(max_length=32)
331        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_HEX:
332            return gen_malicous_hex()
333        case ParamFuzzMode.INT:
334            return gen_num()
335        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_INT:
336            return gen_num(negative_flag=True)
337        case ParamFuzzMode.FLOAT:
338            return gen_num(float_flag=True)
339        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_FLOAT:
340            return gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True)
341        case _:
342            if mode is not ParamFuzzMode.RANDOM:
343                logger.warning(
344                    "Invalid fuzzing mode for parameter EVSEID with type "
345                    "xs:string or xs:hexBinary, using random mode."
346                )
347            invalid_values = []
348            invalid_num = gen_num()
349            invalid_neg_num = gen_num(negative_flag=True)
350            invalid_float_num = gen_num(float_flag=True)
351            invalid_neg_float_num = gen_num(
352                float_flag=True, negative_flag=True
353            )
354            invalid_values.append(invalid_num)
355            invalid_values.append(invalid_neg_num)
356            invalid_values.append(invalid_float_num)
357            invalid_values.append(invalid_neg_float_num)
358
359            if val_type == "string":
360                invalid_string_shorter = gen_random_string(
361                    random.randint(1, 6)
362                )
363                invalid_string_longer = gen_random_string(
364                    random.randint(38, 100)
365                )
366                invalid_values.append(invalid_string_shorter)
367                invalid_values.append(invalid_string_longer)
368            else:
369                # No restriction for min length for hexBinary only for max
370                # Max length for hexBinary is 32
371                invalid_hex_longer = gen_invalid_hex_binary(max_length=32)
372                invalid_values.append(invalid_hex_longer)
373
374            special_string = gen_malicous_string()
375            invalid_values.append(special_string)
376            special_hex = gen_malicous_hex()
377            invalid_values.append(special_hex)
378
379            return random.choice(invalid_values)

def fuzz_parameter( attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[dict] = None) -> dict: 
888def fuzz_parameter(
889    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[dict] = None
890) -> dict:
891    """Fuzz parameter
892
893    Parameter is complex type, so it has attributes and elements.
894    In XSD defined as: parameterType.
895    """
896
897    pairs_name_method = {
898        "@Name": fuzz_parameter_name,
899        "boolValue": fuzz_parameter_bool_value,
900        "byteValue": fuzz_parameter_byte_value,
901        "shortValue": fuzz_parameter_short_value,
902        "intValue": fuzz_parameter_int_value,
903        "physicalValue": fuzz_physical_value_type,
904        "stringValue": fuzz_parameter_string_value,
905    }
906    required_fields = ["@Name"]
907    all_fields = ["@Name"]
908
909    # Based on type add value_type to pairs_name_method
910
911    # Only in conf is "Name", but in XSD is attribute not element
912    # therefor change it to @Name
913    if attr_conf is None:
914        attr_conf = {}
915    if "Name" in attr_conf:
916        attr_conf["@Name"] = attr_conf.pop("Name")
917
918    if "Type" not in attr_conf:
919        attr_conf["Type"] = None
920
921    value_type = fuzz_parameter_type(attr_conf=attr_conf["Type"])
922    required_fields.append(value_type)
923    all_fields.append(value_type)
924    attr_conf.pop("Type")
925    if "Value" in attr_conf:
926        attr_conf[value_type] = attr_conf.pop("Value")
927    else:
928        attr_conf[value_type] = None
929    # After this in attr_conf is only @Name and value_type
930    # value_type is one of the value_types => for ex.:
931    # attr_conf {"@Name": "Port", "intValue": 12}
932
933    res_dict = {}
934    # Call general method for fuzzing complexType
935    res_dict = general_datatype_fuzzing_method(
936        required_fields=required_fields,
937        all_fields=all_fields,
938        attr_conf=attr_conf,
939        valid_values=valid_values,
940        pairs_name_method=pairs_name_method,
941    )
942    return res_dict

Fuzz parameter

Parameter is complex type, so it has attributes and elements. In XSD defined as: parameterType.

def fuzz_gen_challenge( attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None) -> Union[str, int, float]: 
1009def fuzz_gen_challenge(
1010    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None
1011) -> Union[str, int, float]:
1012    """Fuzz gen challenge
1013
1014    GenChallenge is type base64Binary (in xml schema), (length 16).
1015    GenChallenge should be exactly 16 bytes long (128 bits).
1016
1017    From ISO15118-2 example on page 330, length is length of the data before
1018    base64 encoding. Use of UTF-8 encoding is required.
1019    Example: 'U29tZSBSYW5kb20gRGF0YQ==' => 'Some Random Data'
1020    """
1021    # This is end parameter, so there is no passing None/{} to each sub parameter
1022    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, "GenChallenge")
1023
1024    # str to base64 encoding => str to bytes => bytes to base64 encoding
1025    # base64.b64encode(str.encode('utf-8')) or base64.b64encode(bytes(str, 'utf-8'))
1026    # base64 to str => base64 to bytes => bytes to str
1027    # base64.b64decode(base64_encoded_str).decode('utf-8')
1028    # Convert mode to enum
1029
1030    match mode:
1031        case ParamFuzzMode.VALID:
1032            if valid_values is None:
1033                # Generate valid base64 binary, because the length is 16
1034                # => valid value is base64 encoded 16 bytes long binary
1035                return gen_invalid_base64_binary(length=16)
1036            return valid_values
1037        case ParamFuzzMode.LONG_BASE64:
1038            # Generate base64 binary with length > 16
1039            return gen_invalid_base64_binary(max_length=16)
1040        case ParamFuzzMode.SHORT_BASE64:
1041            # Generate base64 binary with length < 16
1042            return gen_invalid_base64_binary(min_length=16)
1043        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_BASE64:
1044            if valid_values is None:
1045                valid_values = gen_invalid_base64_binary(length=16)
1046            return gen_malicous_base64(valid_base64=valid_values)
1047        case ParamFuzzMode.INT:
1048            return gen_num()
1049        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_INT:
1050            return gen_num(negative_flag=True)
1051        case ParamFuzzMode.FLOAT:
1052            return gen_num(float_flag=True)
1053        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_FLOAT:
1054            return gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True)
1055        case ParamFuzzMode.STRING:
1056            return gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 100))
1057        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_STRING:
1058            return gen_malicous_string()
1059        case _:
1060            if mode is not ParamFuzzMode.RANDOM:
1061                logger.warning(
1062                    "Invalid fuzzing mode for parameter with type "
1063                    "base64Binary, using random mode."
1064                )
1065            invalid_values = [
1066                gen_invalid_base64_binary(length=16),
1067                gen_invalid_base64_binary(max_length=16),
1068                gen_invalid_base64_binary(min_length=16),
1069                gen_malicous_base64(),
1070                gen_num(),
1071                gen_num(negative_flag=True),
1072                gen_num(float_flag=True),
1073                gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True),
1074                gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 100)),
1075                gen_malicous_string(),
1076            ]
1077            return random.choice(invalid_values)

1858def fuzz_retry_counter(mode: str = "valid") -> Union[str, int, float]:
1859    """Fuzz retry counter
1860
1861    If the ResponseCode was 'FAILED_NoCertificateAvailable' or 'FAILED_ContractCanceled',
1862    this field contains information, when the EVCC should try to get

1864    Type is xs:short (in xml schema), so valid values: -32768 to 32767, but

1866
1867    The following entries are possible:
1868        x > 0: after x days
1869        0: immediately (at next charging)
1870        -1: never
1871
1872    Use this fuzz method only if ResponseCode is 'FAILED_NoCertificateAvailable'
1873    or 'FAILED_ContractCanceled'.
1874    """

1877    try:
1878        mode = ParamFuzzMode(mode)
1879    except ValueError:
1880        logger.warning(
1881            "Invalid fuzzing mode for RetryCounter, using random mode."
1882        )
1883        mode = ParamFuzzMode.RANDOM
1884
1885    return gen_invalid_short(mode=mode, min_val=-1, max_val=32767)

def fuzz_physical_value_type( modes: Optional[dict], unit_val: str = '', valid_values: Optional[dict] = None) -> dict: 
1969def fuzz_physical_value_type(
1970    modes: Optional[dict],
1971    unit_val: str = "",
1972    valid_values: Optional[dict] = None,
1973) -> dict:
1974    """Fuzz physical value type
1975
1976    PhysicalValueType is complexType.
1977    PhysicalValueType contains 3 fields: Multiplier, Unit, Value.
1978
1979    """
1980    if modes is None:
1981        modes = {}
1982    if valid_values is None:
1983        valid_values = {}
1984
1985    for name in ["Multiplier", "Unit", "Value"]:
1986        # Attribute is not specified in config dict => don't fuzz it
1987        # => valid mode
1988        if name not in modes:
1989            modes[name] = ParamFuzzMode.RANDOM.value
1990        if name not in valid_values:
1991            valid_values[name] = None
1992
1993    multiplier = fuzz_multiplier(
1994        modes["Multiplier"], valid_val=valid_values["Multiplier"]
1995    )
1996    if valid_values["Unit"] is None:
1997        valid_values["Unit"] = unit_val
1998    unit = fuzz_unit(modes["Unit"], valid_val=valid_values["Unit"])
1999    value = fuzz_value(modes["Value"], valid_val=valid_values["Value"])
2000
2001    return {"Multiplier": multiplier, "Unit": unit, "Value": value}

def fuzz_sig_meter_reading(attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None): 
2044def fuzz_sig_meter_reading(
2045    attr_conf: Optional[dict] = None, valid_values: Optional[str] = None
2046):
2047    """Fuzz sig meter reading
2048
2049    SigMeterReading is type xs:base64Binary, maxLength 64.
2050    """
2051    # This is end parameter, so there is no passing None/{} to each sub parameter
2052    mode = get_attr_conf_mode(attr_conf, "SigMeterReading")
2053
2054    match mode:
2055        case ParamFuzzMode.VALID:
2056            if valid_values is None:
2057                logger.warning(
2058                    "No valid value specified for SigMeterReading,"
2059                    "using random value - 1-64 bytes long, base64Binary"
2060                )
2061                return random.randbytes(random.randint(1, 64)).hex()
2062            return valid_values
2063        case ParamFuzzMode.STRING:
2064            return gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 100))
2065        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_STRING:
2066            return gen_malicous_string()
2067        case ParamFuzzMode.LONG_BASE64:
2068            return gen_invalid_base64_binary(max_length=64)
2069        case ParamFuzzMode.SPECIAL_BASE64:
2070            return gen_malicous_base64()
2071        case ParamFuzzMode.INT:
2072            return gen_num()
2073        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_INT:
2074            return gen_num(negative_flag=True)
2075        case ParamFuzzMode.FLOAT:
2076            return gen_num(float_flag=True)
2077        case ParamFuzzMode.NEGATIVE_FLOAT:
2078            return gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True)
2079        case _:
2080            if mode is not ParamFuzzMode.RANDOM:
2081                logger.warning(
2082                    "Invalid fuzzing mode for parameter with type "
2083                    "xs:base64Binary, using random mode."
2084                )
2085            invalid_values = [
2086                gen_random_string(random.randint(1, 100)),
2087                gen_malicous_string(),
2088                gen_invalid_base64_binary(max_length=64),
2089                gen_malicous_base64(),
2090                gen_num(),
2091                gen_num(negative_flag=True),
2092                gen_num(float_flag=True),
2093                gen_num(float_flag=True, negative_flag=True),
2094            ]
2095            return random.choice(invalid_values)
